<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[779,1227,2403,2498]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Skull and external characters: minor-type. Ears, tail, and tibia shorter. Forearm 37-38 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[779,1104,2615,2710]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Details.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[2315,2894,2615,2710]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[2315,2894,2615,2710]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Rh. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter ears, tail, and tibia 
<emphasis box="[1559,1694,2721,2816]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">(cf.</emphasis>
measurements). The forearm is, at least on an average, shorter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[787,1095,2935,3030]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Colour.</emphasis>
♂ ad., skin; Darjeeling; November; teeth unworn. General effect of the colour of the upper side very much as in 
<emphasis box="[677,1277,3151,3246]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[677,1261,3151,3246]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="refulgens">Rh. refulgens</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
though perhaps not quite as dark; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">base of hairs light, 11</emphasis>
ecru-drab 
<emphasis box="[1443,1499,3257,3352]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">”</emphasis>
; under side “ ecru-drab, 
<emphasis box="[2607,2642,3257,3352]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">”</emphasis>
darker on the hinder belly and flanks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[783,1196,3471,3566]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Dentition</emphasis>
(three skulls). p3 in row, almost in row, or external. po and p4 well separated, or almost in contact. p2 in row; a small cusp, pointing inwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" box="[787,1939,3793,3888]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[787,1425,3793,3888]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Measurements.</emphasis>
