<subSubSection lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis box="[793,1485,4001,4096]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Technical name.</emphasis>
Horsfield’s type of 
<emphasis box="[2401,2842,4001,4096]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Rh. minor</emphasis>
is in the British Museum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[665,3622,1531,5274]" lastBlockId="52.[591,3536,589,1962]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[781,971,4215,4310]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[781,930,4215,4310]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Rh.</emphasis>
pusillus
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[967,1507,4215,4310]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">*. —</emphasis>
The figure of the head of 
<emphasis box="[2663,3204,4215,4310]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[2663,3188,4215,4310]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">Rh. pusillus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as given by Temminck, proves that he had before him one of the small species of what is here called the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" box="[2177,2482,4429,4524]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis box="[2177,2482,4429,4524]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (shape of connecting process, of sella, &amp; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1773,1820,4533,4628]" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">c</emphasis>
.). The only question is, therefore, to 
<emphasis box="[677,926,4641,4736]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">which</emphasis>
species the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[1815,2158,4641,4736]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[1815,2158,4641,4736]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs. It would seem to be settled, beyond doubt, by Temminck’s statement that the types were brought from Java. But Dobson, who examined these types in the Leiden Museum, gave the rather astounding information that they are 1 undoubtedly specimens of 
<emphasis box="[2683,3494,5067,5162]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="126">Rh. hipposiderus ”</emphasis>
! t There is only one answer: if so, an interchange of labels has taken place in that Museum; for the Bat figured and described by Temminck as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[1377,1722,697,792]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[1377,1722,697,792]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="127">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was certainly no 
<emphasis box="[2595,3138,697,792]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="127">hipposiderus</emphasis>
; among all the small 
<emphasis box="[1199,1668,803,898]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="127">Rhinolophi</emphasis>
existing it would be difficult to find a stronger to 
<emphasis box="[1502,2041,909,1004]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[1502,2025,909,1004]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">Rh. pusillus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
in the shape of the connecting process, than 
<emphasis box="[1205,1951,1017,1112]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="127">Rh. hipptosiderus.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<footnote pageId="51" pageNumber="126">
